Programming environment Scratch. Other educational programming languages. Creating application for mobile phone. Features of teaching different age groups. Using alternative methods to solve interesting tasks (for example programming games). Planning and conducting Scratch based learning in school and computer club lessons. Changing opinions about programming issues with other students.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the subject is to give an overview of the educational programming languages and prepare participants for the usage of those languages teaching in various school key stages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have passed this course: *enjoy programming; *are able to use all of the functions offered in Scratch environment; *know main functions in at least two other programming environments (e.g. Logo, Alice, Kodu Game Lab); *are able to use various educational programming languages functions to create interesting exercises (e.g. programming computer games); *are able to create a simple application for a mobile phone (MIT App Inventor); *are able to plan and conduct learning process in school or after school computer club lesson, using educational programming languages; *are able to use and create programming materials for various age groups; *are able to describe programming games and out of the computer classroom activities; *are able to do presentations about the educational languages according to the research; *are ready to exchange knowledge about teaching basic programming with other teachers.
